iaturized%20markers%20similar%20to%20what%20actors%20often%20wear%20to%20film%20action%20scenes%20for%20films%20and%20video%20games.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20actually%20gives%20us%20really%20phenomenal%20resolution%20of%20what's%20going%20on%2C%26quot%3B%20Fabian%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20even%20with%20just%20the%20video%20footage%2C%20the%20researchers%20quickly%20saw%20a%20common%20trend%20across%20several%20species%20that%20exhibited%20what%20Fabian%20described%20as%20%26quot%3Bthese%20strange%20paths.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20insects%20would%20turn%20their%20back%20toward%20the%20light%2C%20and%20if%20that%20light%20was%20below%20or%20horizontal%20to%20their%20flight%20path%2C%20it%20often%20caused%20them%20to%20fly%20in%20circles%20or%20crash.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20as%20if%20they%20were%20using%20the%20light%20source%20as%20a%20way%20to%20orient%20themselves%20to%20the%20sky.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20bugs%20get%20too%20close%20to%20artificial%20light%2C%20they%20can%20become%20almost%20trapped%20by%20it%2C%20Peter%20Oboyski%2C%20executive%20director%20and%20collections%20manager%20at%20the%20Essig%20Museum%20of%20Entomology%2C%20who%20wasn't%20involved%20in%20the%20study%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20idea%20that%20they%20want%20their%20dorsal%20surface%2C%20their%20top%20surface%2C%20to%20face%20the%20light%20makes%20a%20lot%20of%20sense%2C%26quot%3B%20Oboyski%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20moth%20with%20a%20red%20marker%20attached%20to%20allow%20researchers%20to%20motion%20capture%20its%20flight%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65b968a27a3d27148875fece%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222666%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EResearchers%20attached%20markers%20to%20the%20backs%20of%20moths%20and%20dragonflies%20to%20capture%20data%20about%20how%20they%20fly%20when%20near%20lights.%3Cp%3ESam%20Fabian%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFish%20exhibit%20similar%20behavior%2C%20Fabian%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bbut%20this%20is%20the%20first%20time%20that%20we%20were%20showing%20that%20this%20was%20happening%20to%20nocturnal%20insects%20around%20artificial%20light.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20researchers%20published%20their%20results%20in%20the%20peer-reviewed%20journal%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3D2292a28ba74d4362714978a5ee293d9a402879a2d1c1a0df499fcfc244989c5a%26postID%3D65b965d4e2d1eb1913181eda%26postSlug%3Dwhy-are-insects-attracted-to-light-new-theory-bugs-2024-1%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.nature.com%252Farticles%252Fs41467-024-44785-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ENature%20Communications%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EInsects%20need%20to%20know%20which%20way%20is%20up%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20animals%20rely%20on%20gravity%20and%20visual%20cues%20to%20orient%20themselves%2C%20Oboyski%20said.%20One%20way%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmosquito-prevention-what-repels-and-attracts-mosquitos-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esome%20insects%3C%2Fa%3E%20stay%20oriented%20is%20by%20using%20something%20called%20dorsal%20light%20response.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20the%20insects%20to%20be%20able%20to%20fly%20level%20to%20the%20ground%20and%20bank%20left%2C%20they%20need%20to%20know%20which%20way%20is%20up%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20A%20reliable%20source%20of%20that%20information%20would%20be%20where%20the%20light%20is%20coming%20from%20%E2%80%94%20the%20sky.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnd%20throughout%20the%20billions%20of%20years%20of%20the%20planet%2C%20that%20would%20be%20up%2C%26quot%3B%20Oboyski%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20confronted%20with%20a%20different%20light%20source%20%E2%80%94%20say%20a%20fire%20from%20below%20or%20a%20headlight%20to%20the%20side%20%E2%80%94%20the%20insects%20try%20to%20face%20the%20top%20of%20their%20body%20toward%20that%20light%20and%20can%20then%20become%20confused%20or%20crash%2C%20Oboyski%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20was%20focused%20on%20insects'%20behavior%20when%20the%20light%20was%20at%20a%20close%20distance%2C%20less%20than%207%20feet%20away.%20It's%20still%20not%20clear%20what%20brings%20them%20there%20in%20the%20first%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20there's%20still%20the%20bigger%20question%20of%20why%20are%20they%20drawn%20to%20the%20light%20from%20further%20distances%2C%20which%20is%20a%20much%20harder%20question%20to%20answer%2C%26quot%3B%20Oboyski%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20moon%20is%20not%20a%20compass%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20many%20theories%20about%20why%20insects%20gather%20at%20lights.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20most%20common%20one%20is%20the%20lunar%20or%20celestial%20navigation%2C%26quot%3B%20Sondhi%20said.%20The%20idea%20is%20that%20insects%20that%20need%20to%20fly%20in%20a%20straight%20line%20can%20use%20the%20position%20of%20the%20moon%20as%20a%20cue.%20They%20mistake%20artificial%20lights%20for%20the%20moon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222566%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20colorful%20insects%20flies%20near%20a%20light%20with%20its%20wings%20spread%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65b96913ac2de4f17ee604f1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221711%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20direction%20of%20the%20light%20affected%20insects%20in%20different%20ways.%20Lights%20facing%20upwards%20or%20placed%20horizontally%20were%20the%20most%20disruptive.%3Cp%3ESam%20Fabian%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Fabian%20said%20they%20tested%20this%20theory%20and%20found%20that%20some%20insects%20started%20traveling%20in%20a%20different%20direction%20when%20a%20new%20light%20source%20switched%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey'd%20actually%20be%20going%20forwards%20and%20backwards%2C%20which%20doesn't%20seem%20like%20the%20kind%20of%20thing%20that%20you%20would%20use%20a%20celestial%20compass%20for%2C%26quot%3B%20Fabian%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EA%20less-bright%20future%20for%20insects%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20a%20reason%20scientists%20have%20long%20sought%20to%20answer%20the%20question%20of%20why%20insects%20are%20attracted%20to%20artificial%20light.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20there%20are%20both%20practical%20reasons%20to%20want%20to%20understand%20this%20and%20also%20theoretical%20reasons%2C%26quot%3B%20Oboyski%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20it%20could%20someday%20help%20us%20prevent%20so%20much%20indiscriminate%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fno-more-insects-disappeared-earth-what-would-happen-2019-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ekilling%20of%20insects%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20lot%20of%20collateral%20damage%20going%20on%20with%20a%20bug%20zapper%2C%26quot%3B%20Oboyski%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20just%20the%20mosquitoes.%26quot%3B%20Figuring%20out%20what%20light%20attracts%20mosquitoes%20%E2%80%94%20and%20only%20mosquitoes%20%E2%80%94%20is%20a%20potential%20benefit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOboyski%20also%20worries%20that%20light%20pollution%20is%20impacting%20the%20way%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcalifornia-monarch-butterfly-migration-photos-show-decline-need-to-protect-2022-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einsects%20navigate%3C%2Fa%3E%20through%20their%20environments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMaybe%20they're%20not%20finding%20mates%20the%20way%20they%20should.%20Maybe%20they're%20not%20finding%20the%20food%20resources%20the%20way%20they%20should%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20Instead%2C%20%26quot%3Bthey're%20getting%20trapped%20in%20the%20realm%20of%20the%20light.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20theoretically%2C%20he%20said%2C%20learning%20more%20about%20insect%20flight%20could%20also%20help%20engineers%20design%20flying%20cars%20one%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20now%2C%20though%2C%20a%20simple%20mitigation%20technique%20would%20be%20to%20