%26quot%3BNetflix%20effect%26quot%3B%20once%20again.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20biggest%20television%20series%20of%202023%2C%20in%20your%20eyes%2C%20might%20have%20been%20%26quot%3BBeef%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3BThe%20Bear%26quot%3B%3A%C2%A0a%20streaming%20original%20with%20a%20prestige%20tint%20and%20a%20bundle%20of%20Emmys%20and%20Golden%20Globes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20last%20year%20was%20actually%20the%20year%20of%20%26quot%3BSuits%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20legal%20drama%20that%20originally%20aired%20on%20USA%20Network%20from%202011%20to%202019%20%E2%80%94%20at%20least%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nielsen.com%2Finsights%2F2024%2Fstreaming-unwrapped-streaming-viewership-goes-to-the-library-in-2023%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENielsen's%202023%20streaming%20data%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20analytics%20firm%20released%20its%20fourth%20annual%20end-of-year%20streaming%20report%2C%20detailing%20the%20top%20television%20series%20and%20movies%20on%20streaming%20platforms%20in%202023.%20As%20a%20caveat%2C%20Nielsen's%20rankings%20are%20by%20minutes%20watched%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0meaning%20that%20longer%20series%20have%20an%20advantage.%20Still%2C%20it's%20noteworthy%20that%20the%20top%2010%20most-watched%20titles%20of%202023%20were%20all%20long-running%20favorites%2C%20the%20vast%20majority%20of%20which%20premiered%20well%20over%20a%20decade%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EComing%20in%20at%20No.%201%20is%20%26quot%3BSuits%26quot%3B%20on%20Netflix%20and%20Peacock%20(57.7%20billion%20minutes).%20%26quot%3BBluey%26quot%3B%20on%20Disney%2B%20(43.9%20billion)%2C%20%26quot%3BNCIS%26quot%3B%20on%20Netflix%20and%20Paramount%2B%20(39.4%20billion)%2C%20%26quot%3BGrey's%20Anatomy%26quot%3B%20on%20Netflix%20(38.6%20billion)%2C%20and%20%26quot%3BCocomelon%26quot%3B%20on%20Netflix%20(36.3%20billion)%20round%20out%20the%20top%20five.%20Other%20titles%20include%20stalwart%20favorites%20like%20%26quot%3BGilmore%20Girls%2C%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BFriend