ontline%20in%20eastern%20Ukraine%20on%20July%2013%2C%202022%2C%20amid%20the%20Russian%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6581d41dcefc010bea24ff85%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222542%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUkrainian%20servicemen%20drive%20a%20T-72%20tank%20on%20the%20frontline%20in%20eastern%20Ukraine%20on%20July%2013%2C%202022%2C%20amid%20the%20Russian%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine.%3Cp%3EMIGUEL%20MEDINA%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EIf%20the%20US%20abandons%20Ukraine%20and%20cuts%20off%20crucial%20aid%2C%20it'll%20be%20a%20historic%20%26quot%3Bown%20goal%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20CIA%20director%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBurns%20wrote%20that%20continuing%20to%20support%20Ukraine%20is%20a%20modest%20investment%20with%20significant%20returns%20for%20the%20US.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EWith%20aid%20tied%20up%20in%20Congress%2C%20the%20US%20and%20Ukraine's%20next%20steps%20have%20critical%20geopolitical%20implications.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EShould%20the%20US%20walk%20away%20from%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine%20and%20abandon%20it%20as%20it%20attempts%20to%20fend%20off%20the%20Russians%2C%20it'll%20be%20it'll%20be%20an%20%26quot%3Bown%20goal%20of%20historic%20proportions%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20CIA%20director%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20warning%20comes%20as%20new%2C%20crucial%20aid%20is%20held%20up%20by%20Republicans%20in%20Congress.%20It%20is%20a%20critical%20time%20for%20the%20US%2C%20which%20has%20contributed%20a%20significant%20amount%20of%20aid%20to%20Ukraine%2C%20to%20question%20its%20vested%20interests%20in%20seeing%20a%20stronger%20Ukraine%20and%20a%20weaker%20Russia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20opinion%20article%20published%20Tuesday%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.foreignaffairs.com%2Funited-states%2Fcia-spycraft-and-statecraft-william-burns%3Futm_medium%3Dpromo_email%26utm_source%3Deditorial_special%26utm_campaign%3Dore_release_Spycraft%2520and%2520Statecraft_prospects_b%26utm_content%3D20240130%26utm_term%3DESPAZ004J3%23author-info%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EForeign%20Affairs%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20CIA%20Director%20William%20J.%20Burns%20wrote%20that%20Putin's%20war%20has%20already%20severely%20impacted%20Russia%20in%20a%20variety%20of%20ways%2C%20from%20isolating%20it%20globally%20to%20damaging%20its%20military%20and%20economy.%20Putin's%20efforts%20to%20modernize%20the%20Russian%20military%2C%20a%20decades-long%20process%2C%20have%20suffered%20as%20a%20result%20of%20this%20devastating%2C%20high-casualty%20conflict.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20CIA%20director%20wrote%20that%20%26quot%3Bat%20least%20315%2C000%20Russian%20soldiers%20have%20been%20killed%20or%20wounded%2C%20two-thirds%20of%20Russia's%20prewar%20tank%20inventory%20has%20been%20destroyed%2C%20and%20Putin's%20vaunted%20decades-long%20military%20modernization%20program%20has%20been%20hollowed%20out.%26quot%3B%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EBurns%20added%20that%20%26quot%3Ball%20this%20is%20a%20direct%20result%20of%20Ukrainian%20soldiers'%20valor%20and%20skill%2C%20backed%20up%20by%20Western%20support.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20war%20isn't%20over%20though.%20Russia%20is%20launching%20offensives%20on%20multiple%20fronts%2C%20and%20despite%20losses%2C%20the%20operations%20continue.%20Russia's%20defense%20industry%20is%20on%20a%20war%20footing%2C%20and%20support%20from%20pariah%20states%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnorth-korea-sitting-pretty-as-russia-china-vie-for-attention-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENorth%20Korea%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20Iran%20is%20fueling%20its%20war%20efforts.%20Ukraine%20is%20holding%20the%20line%2C%20but%20its%20defense%20is%20strained%20by%20shortages%20in%20ammunition%20and%20other%20supplies.Putin%20appears%20to%20be%20gearing%20up%20for%20a%20longer%20war%20that%20will%20require%20Ukraine%20to%20receive%20committed%20and%20stable%20support%20from%20the%20West%20if%20it's%20going%20to%20survive%20the%20fight.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20many%20benefits%20for%20the%20US%20to%20continue%20supporting%20Ukraine%2C%20Burns%20noted%2C%20a%20%26quot%3Brelatively%20modest%20investment%20with%20significant%20geopolitical%20returns.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmong%20other%20benefits%2C%20with%20more%20ammunition%20and%20weapons%20aid%2C%20which%20translates%20to%20a%20greater%20ability%20to%20resist%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EUkraine%20will%20be%20in%20a%20stronger%20position%20should%20it%20opt%20to%20negotiate%20a%20deal%20with%20Russia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20offers%20a%20chance%20to%20ensure%20a%20long-term%20win%20for%20Ukraine%20and%20a%20strategic%20loss%20for%20Russia%3B%20Ukraine%20could%20safeguard%20its%20sovereignty%20and%20rebuild%2C%20while%20Russia%20would%20be%20left%20to%20deal%20with%20the%20enduring%20costs%20of%20Putin's%20folly%2C%26quot%3B%20Burns%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20handout%20image%20shows%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin%2C%20sitting%20and%20gesturing%20with%20one%20hand%20and%20sitting%20in%20front%20of%20a%20blue%20stylised%20world%20map%20as%20he%20takies%20part%20in%20an%20annual%20televised%20phone-in%20with%20the%20country's%20citizens%20dubbed%20%26quot%3BDirect%20Line%20with%20Vladimir%20Putin%26quot%3B%20%20on%20June%2030%2C%202021.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65707bd358e7c0c29a2a0b09%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22617%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20handout%20image%20shows%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin%20taking%20part%20in%20an%20annual%20televised%20phone-in%20with%20the%20country's%20citizens%20dubbed%20%26quot%3BDirect%20Line%20with%20Vladimir%20Putin%26quot%3B%20on%20June%2030%2C%202021.%3Cp%3EAnadolu%2Fhandout%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EA%20weakened%20Russia%20licking%20its%20wounds%20for%20years%20to%20come%20might%20offer%20some%20sense%20of%20peace%20to%20NATO%20members%20and%20other%20nations%20concerned%20about%20an%20increasingly%20aggressive%20Putin%20invading%20them.%20And%20the%20US%20would%20be%20to%20able%20to%20shift%20its%20focus%20to%20tensions%20elsewhere%2C%20such%20as%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-taiwans-election-results-mean-for-relations-with-china-us-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETaiwan%20Strait%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20no%20guarantee%2C%20but%20Burns%20presented%20a%20bleaker%20alternative.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBurns%20wrote%3A%20%26quot%3BFor%20the%20United%20States%20to%20walk%20away%20from%20the%20conflict%20at%20this%20crucial%20moment%20and%20cut%20off%20support%20to%20Ukraine%20would%20be%20an%20own%20goal%20of%20historic%20proportions%2C%26quot%3B%20effectively%20allowing%20Russia%20to%20achieve%20its%20goal%20of%20conquering%20Ukraine%20or%20forcing%20it%20into%20an%20unfavorable%20peace%20deal%2C%20and%20leaving%20Putin%20emboldened%20and%20more%20aggressive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUkrainian%20President%20Volodymyr%20Zelenskyy%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fzelenskyy-russian-threat-will-only-get-worse-if-ukraine-falls-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewarned%20about%20that%20exact%20scenario%20previously%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20including%20to%20US%20lawmakers%20back%20in%20December.%20During%20a%20Washington%2C%20DC%20visit%2C%20the%20Ukrainian%20leader%20pleaded%20for%20more%20US%20aid%20and%20explained%20that%20if%20Russia%20took%20Ukraine%2C%20Putin%20wouldn't%20stop%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESuch%20aggression%20would%20draw%20the%20US%20into%20a%20much%20larger%2C%20costlier%20war%20than%20the%20one%20it's%20supporting%20in%20Ukraine%20right%20now%2C%20experts%20and%20analysts%20have%20argued.%20But%20aid%20is%20still%20held%20up%20in%20Congress.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20latest%20aid%20package%20to%20Ukraine%20has%20been%20on%20hold%20since%20October%2C%20w