rs%20of%20the%20German%20Wehrmacht%20tearing%20down%20the%20border%20crossing%20into%20Poland%2C%201%20September%201939.%20Photo%3A%20Wikimedia%20Commons%2FHans%20S%C3%B6nnke%2FPublic%20Domain.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20postwar%20Germany%20under%20America%E2%80%99s%20thumb%2C%20Anglo-American%20strategy%20focused%20on%20splitting%20China%C2%A0and%20the%20Soviet%20Union.%20On%20the%C2%A0one%20hand%2C%20Britain%20wooed%20Beijing%20and%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20America%20applied%20pressure%20to%20it%2C%20in%20the%201950s.%20This%20carrot-and-stick%20policy%20changed%20in%20the%20late%201960s%20when%20America%20chased%20China%20unabashedly%2C%20culminating%20in%20the%20formal%20Sino-Soviet%20split.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnglo-American%20encouragement%20to%20Ukraine%20to%20take%20on%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20war%20machine%2C%20however%2C%20has%20only%20served%20to%20further%20cement%20Sino-US%20strategic%20relations.%20The%20current%20US%20strategy%20under%20Biden%20differs%20from%20that%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthediplomat.com%2F2017%2F02%2Fwhy-trump-cant-break-russia-away-from-china%2F%5C%22%3EPresident%20Trump%E2%80%99s%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%93%20which%20despite%20the%20latter%E2%80%99s%20crazy%20rhetoric%2C%20followed%20the%20more%20traditional%20divide-and-rule%20strategy%20by%20cosying%20up%20to%20Russia%20while%20applying%20extreme%20pressure%20on%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHalford%20Mackinder%E2%80%99s%20geopolitics%20lives%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConsequently%2C%20Biden%E2%80%99s%20strategy%20has%20merely%20served%20to%20further%20cement%20Sino-Russian%20cooperation%2C%20and%20has%20been%20instrumental%20in%20reinvigorating%20the%20Eurasian%20dream%20by%20exploiting%20the%20latest%20developments%20in%20railroad%20technology.%20They%20are%20now%20practically%20realising%20British%20geopolitical%20theorist%20Halford%20Mackinder%E2%80%99s%20prediction%2C%20in%201904%2C%20that%20the%20inner%20area%20of%20Eurasia%2C%20impenetrable%20by%20sea%20power%2C%20would%20become%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.wikipedia.org%2Fwiki%2FThe_Geographical_Pivot_of_History%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9CPivot%20Area%E2%80%9D%20of%20world%20politics%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Mackinder%E2%80%99s%20prediction%20about%20the%20relative%20decline%20of%20maritime%20power%20due%20to%20the%20superiority%20of%20rail%20over%20ships%20in%20terms%20of%20speed%20and%20penetration%20is%20no%20longer%20far-fetched.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELook%20at%20the%20numbers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fglobalaffairs.org%2Fresearch%2Freport%2Feurasias-freight-infrastructure-vs-russias-war-ukraine%5C%22%3EOnly%2017%20freight%20trains%20%3C%2Fa%3Eran%20from%20China%20to%20Europe%20in%202011.%20Today%20more%20than%2060%2C000%20trains%20cumulatively%20ply%20the%20Eurasian%20landmass%20and%20its%20maritime%20margins.%20Current%20advances%20in%20rail%20technology%20and%20online%20trade%20trends%20that%20demand%20reduced%20delivery%20time%C2%A0%20are%20indicative%20of%20the%20growing%20salience%20of%20transcontinental%20rail%20connectivity%20in%20conduct%20of%20international%20trade.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEurasian%20landmass%20connectivity%20%E2%80%93%20railway%20corridor%20passing%20through%20Kazakhstan%2C%20Russia%2C%20and%20Belarus%20%E2%80%93%20impacts%20the%20overall%20economic%20effects%20of%20American%20naval%20capabilities%20to%20cut%20off%20Chinese%20trade%20and%20supply%20routes%20at%20Malacca%20straits.%C2%A0%20The%20Chinese%20answer%20to%20its%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fgjia.georgetown.edu%2F2023%2F03%2F22%2Fchinas-economic-security-challenge-difficulties-overcoming-the-malacca-dilemma%2F%5C%22%3EMalacca%20Dilemma%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20the%20threat%20of%20a%20naval%20blockade%20of%20vital%20Chinese%20sea%20lines%20of%20communication%20in%20the%20Indian%20Ocean%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%20has%20been%20the%20carving%20out%20of%20alternative%20trade%20routes%20to%20the%20West%2C%20all%20the%20way%20to%20Europe.%20However%2C%20the%20Chinese%20alternative%20trade%20routes%20are%20dependent%20on%20Russian%20cooperation.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2FCEFT%5C%22%3EThe%20China-Europe%20Freight%20Train%20(CEFT)%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20heavily%20dependent%20on%20Russia%20%C2%A0%E2%80%9Cas%20both%20the%20most%20important%20terminus%20and%20through-corridor%20accounting%20for%2037%25%20of%20all%20CEFTs%20through%202021%2C%20leading%20Germany%20at%2024.3%25%20and%20Poland%20at%2023.4%25.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmerica%20did%20not%20tolerate%20Sino-Soviet%20unity%20in%20the%20Cold%20War%2C%20and%20it%20will%20not%20do%20so%20now.%20The%20war%20in%20Europe%20has%20disrupted%20the%20development%20of%20these%20connectivity%20projects%20due%20to%20sanctions%20imposed%20on%20Russia%2C%20thereby%20adversely%20impacting%C2%A0China%E2%80%99s%20long-term%20interests%20in%20the%20Eurasian%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20many%20companies%20operating%20rail%20freight%20between%20China%20and%20the%20EU%20are%20avoiding%20transit%20through%20Russia%2C%20resulting%20in%20greater%20use%20of%20the%20Middle%20Corridor%20(the%20Trans-Caspian%20International%20Transport%20Route)%E2%80%94from%20Southeast%20Asia%20and%20China%20through%20Kazakhstan%2C%20the%20Caspian%20Sea%2C%20Azerbaijan%2C%20and%20Georgia%E2%80%94as%20an%20alternative%20route%2C%20causing%20longer%20journeys%20and%20increased%20costs.%20The%20West%20is%20likely%20to%20support%20Ukraine%E2%80%99s%20fight%20against%20Russia%20until%2C%20of%20course%2C%20the%20latter%20is%20economically%20and%20militarily%20exhausted%20and%20willing%20to%20reassess%20its%20look-east%20policy%20and%C2%A0relationship%20with%20China.%20This%20looks%20a%20long%20way%20off%2C%20and%20promises%20continuation%20of%20the%20%E2%80%9Cforever%20wars%E2%80%9D%20dispensation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20in%20the%20recent%20Pakistan-Iran%20conflict%2C%20what%20has%20come%20to%20light%20is%20the%20involvement%20of%20Balochistan%2C%20with%20the%20Gwadar%20port%20located%20close%20to%20the%20Gulf%20of%20Oman%2C%20an%20important%20link%20in%20the%20new%20silk%20road%20envisaged%20by%20China.%20Damascus%E2%80%94the%20traditional%20terminus%20node%20of%20the%20ancient%20Silk%20Road%E2%80%94is%20also%20embroiled%20in%20a%20conflict%20situation%20and%20is%20a%20pariah%20state%20in%20the%20western%20geopolitical%20equation.%20In%202022%2C%20there%20were%20clashes%20on%20the%20Tajikistan-Kyrgyzstan%20border.%20In%20the%20beginning%20of%202022%2C%20Kazakistan%20witnessed%20violent%20protests%20against%20President%20Kassym-Jomart%20Tokayev%E2%80%99s%20rule.%20The%20Armenia-Azerbaijan%20hostilities%20over%20the%20disputed%20Nagorno-Karabakh%20republic%20provide%20America%20with%20an%20opportunity%20to%20meddle%20in%20Central%20Asia%20to%20put%20pressure%20on%20the%20China-Russia%20alliance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20dawn%20of%20the%2020th%20century%2C%20Germany%E2%80%99s%20plans%20to%20build%20the%20Berlin-Baghdad%20rail%20link%20became%20one%20of%20the%20most%20important%20reasons%20for%20World%20War%20I%2C%20as%20they%20threatened%20the%20British-controlled%20sea%20lanes%20of%20communication%20passing%20through%20the%20Suez%20Canal.%20It%20was%20seen%20as%20part%20of%20an%20inter-imperial%20assault%20on%20the%20British%20empire.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20home%2C%20the%20major%20colonial%20powers%20faced%20growing%20political%20discontent%2C%20economic%20inequality%2C%20mass%20immiseration%2C%20and%20the%20emergence%20of%20powerful%20trade%20union%2C%20worker%2C%20and%20socialist%20movements%20against%20capitalism%20and%20empire.%20A%20world%20war%20resulted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20dawn%20of%20the%2021%20century%2C%20we%20live%20in%20a%20world%20best%20described%20by%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheroadsinitiative.org%2Fpoly-crisis-or-organic-crisis-the-crisis-of-the-united-states-and-the-us-led-world-order%2F%5C%22%3Ecrisis%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%20whether%20called%20%E2%80%9Cpoly%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9Cperma%E2%80%9D%2C%20or%20organic.%20At%20home%20in%20so%20many%20countries%20across%20the%20world%2C%20we%20see%20popular%20resistance%20to%20elite%20rule%2C%20crises%20of%20legitimacy%20and%20authority%2C%20increasing%20political%20polarisation%20and%20violence%2C%20the%20politics%20of%20right-wing%20racist%2C%20and%20communal%20divide%20and%20rule.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGlobally%2C%20the%20geopolitical%20and%20geoeconomic%20cracks%20in%20a%20system%20of%20complex%20interdependence%20are%20evolving%20into%20schisms.%20The%20struggle%20for%20hegemony%20and%20empire%20is%20increasingly%20breaking%20out%20into%20violence.%20The%20world%20appears%20to%20be%20heading%20towards%20another%20major%20war%20on%20a%20global%20scale%20over%20supply%20lines%2C%20alternative%20trade%20routes%2C%20control%20of%20the%20seas%2C%20and%20the%20Eurasian%20landmass.%20Flashpoints%20from%20Ukraine%20to%20Gaza%20to%20Yemen%20to%20Taiwan%20%E2%80%93%20disciplinary%20military%20confrontations%20for%20containment%20on%20the%20borders%20of%20Eurasia%20and%20its%20core%20powers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDr%20Atul%20Bhardwaj%20is%20an%20honorary%20research%20fellow%20in%20the%20department%20of%20international%20politics%20at%20City%2C%20University%20of%20London.%20He%20is%20the%20author%20of%20%3C%2Fem%3EIndia-America%20Relations%20(1942-62)%3A%20Rooted%20in%20the%20Liberal%20International%20Order%20%3Cem%3E(Routledge%2C%202018)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fiparmar%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EInderjeet%20Parmar%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20professor%20of%20international%20politics%20and%20associate%20dean%20of%20research%20in%20the%20School%20of%20Policy%20and%20Global%20Affairs%20at%20City%2C%20University%20of%20London%2C%20a%20fellow%20of%20the%20Academy%20of%20Social%20Sciences%2C%20and%20a%20columnist%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3EThe%20Wire%3Cem%3E.%20He%20is%20an%20International%20Fellow%20at%20the%20ROADS%20Initiative%20think%20tank%2C%20Islamabad%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3Eand%20author%20of%20several%20books%20including%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3EFoundations%20of%20the%20American%20Century%3Cem%3E.%20He%20is%20currently%20writing%20a%20book%20on%20the%20history%2C%20politics%2C%20and%20powers%20of%20the%20US%20Foreign%20Policy%20Establishment.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706614216000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F20120344%2FAnti-terrorist_operation_in_eastern_Ukraine_War_Ukraine_26894689722.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fflashpoints-in-ukraine-gaza-yemen-and-taiwan-point-to-a-global-war-in-the-making%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Globally%2C%20the%20geopolitical%20and%20geoeconomic%20cracks%20in%20a%20system%20of%20complex%20interdependence%20are%20evolving%20into%20schisms.%20The%20world%20appears%20to%20be%20heading%20towards%20another%20major%20war%20on%20a%20global%20scale%20over%20supply%20lines%2C%20alternative%20trade%20routes%2C%20control%20of%20the%20seas%2C%20and%20the%20Eurasian%20landmass.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fflashpoints-in-ukraine-gaza-yemen-and-taiwan-point-to-a-global-war-in-the-making%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22In%20pics%3A%20Connection%20between%20your%20fav%20food%20brands%20and%20US%20prisons%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706613626000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-107263227%2Cimgsize-1288001.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Ffrom-prison-to-plates-the-hidden-connection-between-your-favorite-food-brands-and-us-prisons%2Fphotostory%2F107263227.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F107263227.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EA%20hidden%20path%20to%20America's%20dinner%20tables%20begins%20here%2C%20at%20an%20unlikely%20source%20%E2%80%93%20a%20former%20Southern%20slave%20plantation%20that%20is%20now%20the%20country's%20largest%20maximum-security%20prison.%20In%20a%20sweeping%20two-year%20investigation%2C%20The%20Associated%20Press%20found%20goods%20linked%20to%20US%20prisoners%20wind%20up%20in%20the%20supply%20chains%20of%20a%20dizzying%20array%20of%20products%20from%20Frosted%20Flakes%20cereal%20and%20Ball%20Park%20hot%20dogs%20to%20Gold%20Medal%20flour%20and%20Coca-Cola.%20They%20are%20on%20the%20shelves%20of%20most%20supermarkets%2C%20including%20Kroger%2C%20Target%2C%20Aldi%2C%20and%20Whole%20Foods.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Ffrom-prison-to-plates-the-hidden-connection-between-your-favorite-food-brands-and-us-prisons%2Fphotostory%2F107263227.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm-timesofindia-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Ffrom-prison-to-plates-the-hidden-connection-between-your-favorite-food-brands-and-us-prisons%2Famp_etphotostory%2F107263227.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Ffrom-prison-to-plates-the-hidden-connection-between-your-favorite-food-brands-and-us-prisons%2Famp_etphotostory%2F107263227.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Ladakh%3A%20Local%20Herders%20Clash%20With%20Chinese%20Soldiers%20Over%20Access%20to%20Grazing%20Land%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F30163202%2FIMG_5078.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Tension%20continues%20to%20prevail%20in%20a%20remote%20border%20region%20in%20Ladakh%20after%20local%20herders%20reportedly%20pelted%20stones%20at%20a%20Chinese%20Army%20patrolling%20unit%20earlier%20this%20month%2C%20after%20they%20were%20allegedly%20denied%20access%20to%20their%20traditional%20grazing%20lands.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELocals%20and%20officials%20said%20that%20the%20clash%20took%20place%20on%20January%202%20in%20Kakjung%20area%20of%20Nyoma%20village%20in%20Chushul%20Valley%20of%20Ladakh%2C%20which%20borders%20the%20Tibet%20region%20controlled%20by%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20group%20of%20local%20herders%20were%20intercepted%20at%20Patrolling%20Point%2035%2C%2036%20and%2037%20in%20Dungti%20village%20of%20Nyoma%20along%20the%20border%20with%20China%20by%20at%20least%20a%20dozen%20visibly%20unarmed%20soldiers%20of%20People%E2%80%99s%20Liberation%20Army%20(PLA)%2C%20who%20were%20also%20accompanied%20by%20three%20armoured%20vehicles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20video%20clip%20of%20the%20clash%2C%20which%20has%20been%20verified%20by%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20was%20shared%20by%20Kunsang%20Namjal%2C%20an%20Instagram%20user%2C%20which%20shows%20a%20herder%20using%20a%20rope%20as%20a%20sling%20to%20pelt%20stones%20at%20the%20incoming%20PLA%20vehicles%2C%20while%20the%20PLA%20soldiers%20and%20other%20herders%20purportedly%20ask%20him%20to%20calm%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhy%20have%20you%20come%20here%3F%20Why%20have%20you%20brought%20your%20vehicles%20here%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20herder%20can%20be%20seen%20shouting%20at%20a%20PLA%20soldier%20in%20Tibetan%20language%2C%20as%20the%20siren%20of%20one%20of%20the%20PLA%20armoured%20vehicles%20blares%20in%20the%20background.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20continued%3A%20%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20our%20ancestral%20land.%20We%20graze%20our%20livestock%20here.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%209-minute%2C%2050-second%20video%20shows%20the%20PLA%20soldiers%20and%20the%20herders%20getting%20into%20a%20heated%20argument%20as%20they%20come%20face%20to%20face.%20The%20video%20shows%20one%20batch%20of%20Chinese%20soldiers%2C%20led%20by%20an%20armoured%20vehicle%2C%20pushing%20the%20herders%20and%20their%20livestock%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20PLA%20soldier%20can%20also%20be%20seen%20blocking%20the%20camera%20lens%20of%20the%20herder%2C%20who%20is%20shooting%20the%20incident%2C%20even%20as%20his%20fellow%20soldiers%20around%20him%20continue%20to%20film%20the%20incident%20while%20waving%20at%20the%20herders%20to%20move%20out%20of%20the%20area.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20a%20visibly-agitated%20herder%2C%20who%20breaks%20from%20the%20scene%2C%20pulls%20out%20a%20sling%20from%20beneath%20his%20coat%2C%20puts%20a%20stone%20in%20it%20and%20swings%20it%20at%20the%20incoming%20armoured%20vehicle%2C%20which%20visibly%20escaped%20the%20hit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20reached%20out%20to%20Deputy%20Commissioner%20Leh%20Santosh%20Sukhadeva%20and%20SSP%20Leh%20for%20their%20comment%20about%20the%20development.%20This%20article%20will%20be%20updated%20when%20they%20respond.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChushul%20Councillor%20Konchok%20Stanzin%2C%20who%20posted%20the%20video%20on%20X%2C%20formerly%20Twitter%2C%20said%20that%20nomads%20put%20up%20a%20brave%20face%20when%20the%20PLA%20soldiers%20stopped%20their%20livestock%20from%20grazing.%20%E2%80%9CLivelihoods%20of%20locals%20have%20been%20taken%20away%20in%20the%20name%20of%20buffer%20zones%20and%20patrolling%20points.%20Our%20nomads%20are%20struggling%20for%20their%20land%2C%E2%80%9D%20Stanzin%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20clash%2C%20the%20herders%20were%20forced%20to%20move%20out%20of%20the%20area%2C%20sparking%20anger%20in%20the%20nomadic%20community%20who%20depend%20on%20the%20pastures%20in%20the%20highlands%20of%20Ladakh%20for%20their%20survival.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20not%20the%20first%20time%20Chinese%20soldiers%20have%20turned%20away%20nomads%20from%20their%20traditional%20lands%20in%20Ladakh.%20In%20the%20past%2C%20there%20have%20been%20several%20reports%20of%20incursion%20by%20China%20with%20Indian%20patrols%20also%20reportedly%20losing%20access%20to%20the%20strategic%20Depsang%20Plains%2C%20Demchok%20and%20other%20areas%20in%20eastern%20Ladakh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20opposition%20led%20by%20the%20Congress%20has%20accused%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%20of%20covering%20up%20%E2%80%9Cterritorial%20setbacks%E2%80%9D%20in%20Ladakh%2C%20while%20the%20Union%20government%20has%20denied%20the%20charges%20as%20%E2%80%9Cpolitically%20motivated%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20a%20landmark%20built%20by%20the%20Indian%20Army%20at%20the%20site%20of%20the%20Rezang%20La%20battle%20of%20the%201962%20Sino-India%20conflict%20in%20Ladakh%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Frezang-la-battle-landmark-removed-as-part-of-disengagement-councillor-says%5C%22%3Ewas%20dismantled%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20part%20of%20the%20disengagement%20process%20with%20China%2C%20prompting%20anger%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDiplomatic%20and%20military%20level%20talks%20on%20the%20border%20dispute%20between%20the%20two%20countries%20have%20failed%20to%20make%20any%20significant%20headway%20in%20recent%20years%20as%20relations%20between%20the%20two%20South%20Asian%20giants%20has%20soured%20over%20New%20Delhi%E2%80%99s%20growing%20camaraderie%20with%20Washington.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFollowing%20the%20Galwan%20Valley%20clashes%20which%20brought%20the%20two%20South%20Asian%20giants%20on%20the%20brink%20of%20a%20full-blown%20war%20in%202020-2021%2C%20traditional%20grazing%20land%20has%20turned%20into%20a%20buffer%20zone%20at%20many%20places%20in%20Ladakh%2C%20increasing%20the%20difficulties%20of%20nomadic%20herders.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20Stimson%20Centre%2C%20a%20Washington-based%20online%20policy%20platform%2C%20the%20lack%20of%20a%20clear%20demarcation%20of%20the%20border%20between%20India%20and%20China%20and%20continuing%20Chinese%20incursions%20in%20Chushul%2C%20Chumur%2C%20Dungti%2C%20Phobrang%2C%20and%20Demchok%20has%20adversely%20affected%20the%20life%20of%20Changpas%2C%20a%20nomadic%20community%20which%20lives%20along%20the%20Line%20of%20Actual%20Control%20in%20Ladakh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20conflict%20and%20the%20lack%20of%20development%20in%20border%20villages%20have%20forced%20many%20to%20flee%20to%20the%20town%20of%20Leh%20and%20thus%20the%20looming%20danger%20of%20mass%20migration%20from%20the%20border%20villages%20requires%20timely%20intervention%20by%20the%20Indian%20government%20and%20an%20inclusive%20Ladakh%20policy%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20centre%20noted%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsouthasianvoices.org%2Fassessing-the-human-impact-of-the-india-china-border-dispute%2F%5C%22%3Ereport%20in%20its%C2%A0%3Cem%3ESouth%20Asian%20Voices%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0journal%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706612848000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F30163202%2FIMG_5078.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Fladakh-local-herders-clash-with-chinese-solders-over-access-to-grazing-land%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Locals%20and%20officials%20said%20that%20the%20clash%20took%20place%20on%20January%202%20in%20the%20Kakjung%20area%20of%20Nyoma%20village%20in%20Chushul%20Valley%2C%20Ladakh%2C%20which%20borders%20the%20Tibet%20region.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A17%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Fladakh-local-herders-clash-with-chinese-solders-over-access-to-grazing-land%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Ex-IRS%20contractor%20gets%205%20yrs%20in%20prison%20for%20leak%20of%20tax%20return%20info%20of%20Trump%2C%20rich%20people%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706612610000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-107262612%2Cimgsize-37468.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fexirs-contractor-gets-5-years-in-prison-for-leaking-tax-return-info-of-trump-rich-people%2Farticleshow%2F107262626.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%