%20British%20had%20to%20leave%20the%20country%20and%20we%20gained%20our%20freedom.%20But%2C%20freedom%20came%20at%20the%20cost%20of%20partition%20of%20the%20country.%20The%20moment%20of%20the%20celebration%20of%20freedom%20was%20marred%20by%20widespread%20communal%20violence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20(During)%20that%20crisis%2C%20when%20the%20leaders%20of%20the%20freedom%20movement%20were%20hoisting%20the%20Indian%20flag%20in%20Delhi%2C%20Gandhiji%20was%20in%20remote%20villages%20dousing%20communal%20violence%20and%20bringing%20solace%20to%20the%20victims%20of%20the%20riots.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20trying%20to%20bring%20unity%20among%20the%20Hindus%20and%20Muslims%20Gandhiji%20was%20assassinated%20by%20a%20Nathuram%20Godse%2C%20a%20Hindu%20fanatic%20with%20known%20links%20to%20rabid%20Hindu%20nationalist%20organisations%20on%2030%20January%201948%20at%20Birla%20House%2C%20Delhi.%20The%20country%20was%20shocked.%20The%20world%20was%20shocked.%20But%20immediately%20the%20communal%20riots%20stopped.%20Through%20his%20martyrdom%2C%20Gandhiji%20brought%20peace%20to%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20then%20India%20has%20been%20observing%2030%20January%20as%20a%20Martyrs%20Day%20every%20year%20in%20his%20memory.%20However%2C%20since%202014%20the%20present%20regime%20has%20been%20tacitly%20trying%20to%20undermine%20Gandhiji%20and%20his%20legacy.%20But%2C%20we%20think%20in%20today%E2%80%99s%20India%2C%20Gandhian%20principles%20have%20become%20more%20relevant%20than%20before.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGandhiji%20was%20a%20deeply%20religious%20person%20and%20a%20devout%20Hindu.%20But%20for%20him%20the%20essence%20of%20religion%20was%20justice.%20He%20never%20compromised%20with%20the%20principles%20of%20truth%2C%20nonviolence%20and%20justice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELet%20us%20uphold%20these%20principles%20and%20remember%20Gandhiji%20on%2030%20January%20when%20the%20country%20is%20immersed%20in%20the%20gloom%20of%20divisive%20politics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESignatories%3C%2Fp%